Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the
@garlic{2%cloves} and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @water{1¾%cups},
@chicken stock concentrate{1}, @turmeric{1%tsp}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Bring to a boil.

Once mixture in pot boils, add @jasmine rice{1%cup} and stir once. Cover pot and
lower heat to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered
off heat. Meanwhile, core and deseed @bell pepper{2}, then cut into thin strips.
Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{4}, separating greens and whites. Quarter
@lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
bell peppers and cook, tossing, until just softened and starting to char,
~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer slices to a #bowl{}
or #plate{} and set aside.

Tear @pulled chicken{16%oz} into bite-sized pieces. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and
remaining garlic. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Toss in chicken and
@cumin{2%tsp}. Cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Stir @tomato paste{3%oz} into pan with chicken. Cook, stirring, for
~{1%minute}. Add @water{1½%cups}, remaining @chicken stock concentrate{2 - 0.5%unit},
and @hot smoked paprika{1%tsp}. Bring to a simmer and let bubble, stirring
occasionally, until liquid has reduced to a thick, saucy consistency. Stir in
bell peppers and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with plenty of @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Divide between plates and top with chicken mixture. Garnish with
scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon quarters on the side for squeezing
over.